The national executive committee (NEC) of the African National Congress (ANC) is ready to have a successful national policy conference, party s spokesperson Zizi Kodwa said. We have adopted the rules, adopted the programme and everything else which will make the policy conference run smoothly,&#8221; Kodwa said.He said the NEC has approved the programmes due to start on today (Friday).Meanwhile there are reports that some branches in the Western Cape are sending parallel delegates to the policy conference.&#8220;For the past weeks we have been working from Nasrec. We are waiting for the delegates to arrive,&#8221; Kodwa added.-Sipho Jack&nbsp;